  "text": "Despite such legalized barriers to education, educational possibilities for African-Americans in the South increased markedly over the course of the 20 th century. This time-period effect engendered dissimilar educational opportunities, on average, for different age cohorts now alive [CITATION_1] . For example, AfricanAmericans who are currently in their 80s experienced a different educational climate when they were school-aged than did those who are now in their 40s.",
